Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1007 \N"Out For Revenge (Part One)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.94,0:00:11.32,Haruyama,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,393)}Haruyama Junpei (37)\NCafé Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.61,0:00:12.07,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The victim is Haruyama \NJunpei-san, 37 years old,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.07,0:00:14.74,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,who operates a café by the train station.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.98,0:00:18.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed last night around 9 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.55,0:00:23.61,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We believe he was attacked after closing his\Nshop and heading towards his home past this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.48,0:00:29.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, he was stabbed repeatedly.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.38,0:00:33.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's safe to assume the \Nsuspect's motive is a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.88,0:00:34.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.26,0:00:37.95,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Gather information from the locals and—
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.44,0:00:41.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.61,0:00:42.50,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.50,0:00:46.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing. I just thought {\i1}he{\i0} might show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.96,0:00:51.28,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, gather information and \Ndraw up a list of his acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.28,0:00:52.03,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.61,0:00:57.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.27,0:00:59.53,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.53,0:01:01.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Curtains rise on a man's quest for revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.46,0:01:03.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Follow that suspect! Where is he now?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.48,0:01:05.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.14,0:01:07.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.00,0:01:09.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.02,0:02:57.03,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,1)}Out For Revenge \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.75,0:02:54.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Out For Revenge, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.07,0:03:06.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It's on the fifth floor of this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.62,0:03:10.41,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.96,0:03:15.42,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}knew{\i0} he'd show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:18.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Are you here on a case?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.24,0:03:21.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're gathering information for that \Ncase that was on the news, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.56,0:03:23.18,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.49,0:03:26.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,One of the victim's friends \Nis inside this building.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.44,0:03:29.65,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.65,0:03:32.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then allow me to assist you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.33,0:03:33.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.92,0:03:47.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You must be Natsukawa Yoji-san, \Nthe investment consultant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.08,0:03:51.50,Natsukawa,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,436)}Natsukawa Yoji (40)\NInvestment Consultant
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.77,0:03:50.32,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes, that's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:53.00,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What business do the police have with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.14,0:03:56.99,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like to ask you a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.99,0:03:58.91,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Would that be all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:02.03,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.50,0:04:10.77,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You have guests.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:14.62,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Don't mind them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.22,0:04:15.90,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.09,0:04:17.52,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to ask me?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.14,0:04:21.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You've probably already seen it on the news,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.86,0:04:27.07,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but your friend Haruyama Junpei-san \Nwas found murdered this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.17,0:04:34.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.47,0:04:38.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like your guests \Nknew Haruyama-san, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.28,0:04:42.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but who are you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.89,0:04:44.38,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,We've got nothing to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.38,0:04:47.80,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,I was just thinking about how I'd \Nheard that story on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.98,0:04:50.22,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,For reference, could we get your names?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.61,0:04:57.12,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}My name is Fuyuki Ryuzaburo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.69,0:04:58.61,Fuyuki,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,438)}Fuyuki Ryuzaburo (40)\NFinance Business Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.12,0:04:59.61,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I make a meager living in finance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:01.11,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm Akiba Miyako.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:02.86,Miyako,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(401,433)}Akiba Miyako (42)\NReal Estate Business Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.11,0:05:02.74,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I work in real estate.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:08.35,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Neither of them are on our \Nlist of acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.35,0:05:09.49,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.07,0:05:11.91,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,What did you want to ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.11,0:05:17.39,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know anyone who may have held a \Ngrudge against the late Haruyama-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.08,0:05:20.78,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,There wasn't anyone like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.78,0:05:22.67,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,What about you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.85,0:05:23.92,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.92,0:05:27.18,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anyone named Haruyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.43,0:05:29.05,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You guys...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.29,0:05:32.93,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I knew Haruyama,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.30,0:05:35.61,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,the murder happened last night, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.18,0:05:40.19,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If you investigate my whereabouts at that \Ntime, you'll find that I have an alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.63,0:05:43.16,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I have nothing to do with the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.16,0:05:44.32,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Likewise.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.85,0:05:47.68,DCMain,NATSUKAWA,0000,0000,0000,,It would be wise to take your \Ninvestigation elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.51,0:05:57.83,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Those three are hiding something.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.13,0:06:00.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Most likely.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.65,0:06:03.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why hide what they know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.53,0:06:06.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They're either protecting the culprit
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.22,0:06:10.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,or there's some reason why they can't tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.64,0:06:19.81,The Next Day,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(404,1)\blur2}The Next Day
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.06,0:06:21.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.12,0:06:27.48,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the truth out \Nof him for the inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.48,0:06:30.20,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He did throw up a smokescreen yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.04,0:06:35.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This place is both a residence \Nand office, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:36.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.36,0:06:38.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Did he go out this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.80,0:06:42.71,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.52,0:06:49.79,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Natsukawa-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.05,0:06:52.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Natsukawa-san, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.68,0:06:54.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.94,0:06:57.10,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, call the inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.30,0:06:58.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:11.23,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As we told you earlier, last night,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.23,0:07:14.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Natsukawa Yoji-san was murdered as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.73,0:07:18.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He was killed in the same \Nmanner as Haruyama-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.62,0:07:23.46,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Fuyuki-san and Akiba-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.46,0:07:26.88,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,you know why we asked you \Nto come here, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.01,0:07:34.01,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to tell us \Neverything you've been hiding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.84,0:07:36.23,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.23,0:07:40.39,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn't a groundless fear after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.70,0:07:46.64,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,If both Haruyama and Natsukawa have \Nbeen killed, then it must be him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.04,0:07:49.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Him, who?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.10,0:07:52.52,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.26,0:07:55.03,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto Takashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:08:01.41,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Who is this Komoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.35,0:08:08.19,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Haruyama, Natsukawa, and the two of us got \Nto know each other as regulars at a bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.19,0:08:10.96,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,That was ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.30,0:08:14.76,The Next Day,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(482,350)\pos(323,270)\blur2\3c&H17181C&}10 Years Ago
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.69,0:08:16.48,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}The four of us had dreams and \Nambitions, but we lacked the cash.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.81,0:08:21.62,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We told each other that if only we \Nhad the capital, we'd manage somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.42,0:08:24.92,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when Fuyuki made a suggestion.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.68,0:08:29.90,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,"I have a high school classmate \Nnamed Komoto Takashi."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.22,0:08:33.98,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,"He inherited a huge amount \Nof money from his parents."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.98,0:08:37.03,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Let's swindle him out of his money."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.37,0:08:41.69,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,"He's a naïve rich boy. \NI guarantee it'll work."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.33,0:08:46.04,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We presented him with a \Nbogus investment opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.26,0:08:50.05,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,and split the money we swindled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.59,0:08:55.55,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We even hired a lawyer to cover up our fraud.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.28,0:09:00.50,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He must have lost hope after being \Nbetrayed by a former classmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:04.67,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He left Japan and moved to South America.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.16,0:09:07.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.98,0:09:10.82,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the four of you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.44,0:09:15.70,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,ganged up on Komoto and preyed upon him.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.10,0:09:18.95,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That was ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.66,0:09:24.00,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,B-But the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.04,0:09:28.21,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,we received a frightened call from Haruyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:31.72,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,He said Komoto was peering into his shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.72,0:09:35.88,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,He thought he may have returned \Nto Japan to get revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.30,0:09:39.30,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But the three of us laughed it off,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.30,0:09:41.66,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,saying it must've been someone \Nelse and that he was imagining it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.42,0:09:45.98,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,But then we saw on the news that \NHaruyama had been murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.62,0:09:49.46,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,We thought it might actually be Komoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.46,0:09:54.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So the three of you gathered \Nbecause you were worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.60,0:09:57.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They must've been right \Nin the middle of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.06,0:10:01.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's when we visited \NNatsukawa with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.76,0:10:05.38,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,And now that Natsukawa has \Nbeen murdered as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.38,0:10:10.63,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto's the only guy who \Nresented Haruyama and Natsukawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:13.55,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Confirm their story ASAP.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.55,0:10:14.42,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.52,0:10:20.89,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be asking you for more \Ndetails down at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.89,0:10:26.89,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\fs26\org(365,35)\frx14\fry354\shad2\bord2\c&H1AC8DE&\3c&H5389A0&\4c&H106580&\pos(365,37)\frz19.06\blur1}MPD Beika Police Station
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.50,0:10:31.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,According to the Immigration Bureau, one \Nweek ago, Komoto Takashi returned to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.06,0:10:33.19,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.54,0:10:38.86,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He's already checked out, but we also \Nfound the hotel where he was staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.86,0:10:43.20,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,We were able to collect Komoto's \Nfingerprints from the belongings he left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.48,0:10:45.20,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.71,0:10:51.91,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,They matched the fingerprints collected from \Nthe scenes of both Haruyama's and Natsukawa's murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:55.50,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,So Komoto is the murderer, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:10:57.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We also found this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.06,0:11:01.68,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This is an image of Komoto Takashi \Ncaptured by the hotel's security cameras.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.38,0:11:01.30,Komoto,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(403,432)}Komoto Takashi (40)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.44,0:11:04.84,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,This is what he looks like now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.84,0:11:07.43,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,His hair is snow white.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.57,0:11:11.31,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Also, Komoto apparently said to an employee
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.77,0:11:15.44,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,that he has an incurable illness \Nand doesn't have long to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.83,0:11:20.33,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:23.65,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,With death approaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.65,0:11:27.86,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto returned to Japan and \Nmurdered Haruyama and Natsukawa,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.86,0:11:32.71,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,the men who betrayed him, one after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.87,0:11:36.09,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.67,0:11:39.11,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,He must be crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.56,0:11:42.59,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Why get revenge now for something \Nthat happened ten years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.89,0:11:45.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I was curious about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.70,0:11:48.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,so I asked the local police about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.75,0:11:51.47,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of his motive,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.47,0:11:54.98,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,we can't allow him to kill anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.72,0:12:00.56,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You'll act as their bodyguards and do \Nwhatever it takes to find Komoto Takashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.56,0:12:01.27,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.19,0:12:05.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's a brutal serial murder case,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.24,0:12:07.53,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but there's nothing left for me to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.03,0:12:10.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, seems that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.75,0:12:21.13,The Next Day,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(445,390)\blur2\3c&H17181C&\pos(321,265)}The Next Day
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:25.18,The Next Day,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(441,395)\blur2\3c&H17181C&\pos(321,266)}Shikigawa Valley
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.06,0:12:31.56,The Uedas,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(397,1)}The Uedas
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.11,0:12:44.54,DCMain,SHIMODA MAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}See? It's a little scary, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.15,0:12:45.16,The Shimodas,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(403,438)}The Shimodas
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.54,0:12:48.55,DCMain,SHIMODA WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}But the view is incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.55,0:12:50.28,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:55.13,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I know I shouldn't be out walking around,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.13,0:12:58.25,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,but my client wanted to meet outdoors.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.25,0:12:59.86,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.31,0:13:02.67,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I need to check out the area beforehand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:05.91,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.43,0:13:19.39,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Now this is a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.62,0:13:26.67,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Akiba-san, I'm going to \Ngo check out that noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.67,0:13:27.96,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Stay there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.22,0:13:47.35,DCMain,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Akiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.36,0:13:51.18,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,K-Komoto...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.85,0:13:55.05,DCMain,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It's all...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.55,0:13:57.81,DCMain,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It's all your guys' fault!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.40,0:14:01.48,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.48,0:14:04.82,DCMain,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Die!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.25,0:14:18.25,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Akiba-san! What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:20.50,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,K-Komoto just fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.74,0:14:22.80,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,What? Komoto fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.45,0:14:45.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he survived \Na fall from that height.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.09,0:14:45.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.21,0:14:49.53,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying this is what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:52.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You were lured away by \Na noise in the thicket.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.76,0:14:54.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,While you were looking elsewhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.54,0:15:01.34,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto attacked Akiba-san, and after a \Nstruggle, Komoto's foot slipped and he fell.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.34,0:15:02.78,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.83,0:15:07.17,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't see the moment Komoto fell?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.37,0:15:09.53,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.53,0:15:14.62,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Are you trying to say I pushed him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.62,0:15:16.92,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.92,0:15:18.35,DCMain,SHIMODA MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.93,0:15:21.79,DCMain,SHIMODA MAN,0000,0000,0000,,She's telling the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.79,0:15:25.51,DCMain,SHIMODA WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,That man accidentally fell by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.02,0:15:27.79,DCMain,UEDA MAN,0000,0000,0000,,We saw it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.79,0:15:28.32,DCMain,UEDA WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.51,0:15:30.32,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.73,0:15:33.49,DCMain,UEDA MAN,0000,0000,0000,,That person must've seen it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.49,0:15:34.47,DCMain,UEDA MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.47,0:15:36.83,DCMain,UEDA WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're not here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:39.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like there's several witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.98,0:15:45.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. In other words, Komoto Takashi \Naccidentally fell to his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.88,0:15:47.52,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:49.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But where is the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.80,0:15:53.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is it possible that he survived and fled?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:58.66,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,It did take us a while to get down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.66,0:16:01.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying he disappeared \Nduring that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.63,0:16:03.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.42,0:16:06.36,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But a fall from this height?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.61,0:16:11.65,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, how did Komoto get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.01,0:16:16.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a rental car that Komoto \Nseems to have driven here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.43,0:16:22.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then if he survived, even if he was injured,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.80,0:16:25.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,wouldn't he have used that car to flee?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.37,0:16:31.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he was so badly injured \Nthat he couldn't drive a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.15,0:16:33.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.31,0:16:36.44,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, I'll check out \Nthe hospitals in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.44,0:16:37.60,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.50,0:16:40.68,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What a waste of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:44.19,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he survived a fall from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.40,0:16:47.44,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I can go now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.86,0:16:49.93,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,That should be fine. Chiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.93,0:16:50.73,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.73,0:16:51.44,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.70,0:16:53.72,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need a bodyguard anymore, do I?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.72,0:16:55.61,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's dead now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.81,0:16:57.38,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's just to be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.38,0:16:59.12,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,He'll escort you home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.11,0:17:01.56,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.30,0:17:09.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Now that the suspect is \Ndead, the case is closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.85,0:17:12.76,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It's not what I would've wanted, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.28,0:17:15.54,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,I know what Takagi said,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.54,0:17:19.87,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,but it's hard to believe he \Nsurvived a fall from up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.62,0:17:21.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.43,0:17:26.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why haven't they found a body?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.69,0:17:29.52,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't look that deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.57,0:17:33.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be odd if the body got caught \Non the rocks at the bottom of the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.53,0:17:37.45,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs30\shad2\4c&H3F424E&\c&HEFFCF7&\3c&HA2B7C2&\fnTimes New Roman\bord2}Shikigawa General Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.45,0:17:39.99,Returning Patients,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(630,73,735,73)}Returning Patients
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.45,0:17:43.95,Accounting,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(50,79,275,80)}Accounting
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.45,0:17:43.95,Admissions,SIGN MIDDLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(320,80,540,80)}Admissions
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.78,0:17:39.29,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.29,0:17:41.83,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No injured patients matching \Nthat description have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.44,0:17:43.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.85,0:17:45.80,DCMain,NURSE,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a police detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.80,0:17:46.82,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.82,0:17:51.89,DCMain,NURSE,0000,0000,0000,,If you're looking for him, then is he \Nthe suspect in a case or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.89,0:17:52.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.14,0:17:55.56,DCMain,NURSE,0000,0000,0000,,In that case, I hope you find him soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.04,0:17:58.59,DCMain,NURSE,0000,0000,0000,,It would be terrible if he did anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.59,0:17:59.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.17,0:18:06.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Inspector Megure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.02,0:18:11.16,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't find anything. Komoto \Nhasn't shown up at the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.06,0:18:18.55,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto destroyed himself, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.99,0:18:24.20,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,He fell headfirst and screamed \Nall the way down to hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.47,0:18:29.20,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, you and I survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.20,0:18:31.09,DCMain,MIYAKO,0000,0000,0000,,We have the devil's luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.59,0:18:44.56,The Next Day,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(404,396)\bord1\blur2\3c&H17181C&\shad1}2 Days Later
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.34,0:18:54.90,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Stabbed repeatedly with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.90,0:18:56.57,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Same method.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.37,0:18:58.63,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,T.K.?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.80,0:19:02.46,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto Takashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.25,0:19:16.62,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Akiba-san was murdered \Nlast night around 11 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.62,0:19:22.84,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto Takashi's fingerprints were found \Non the lighter left next to the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.16,0:19:27.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So Komoto survived his fall from that cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.61,0:19:31.35,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,And he has resumed his revenge murders.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.90,0:19:34.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.85,0:19:39.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I've learned why Komoto sought revenge now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.31,0:19:42.42,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,When he first moved to South America,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.42,0:19:47.58,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto Takashi sometimes lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.13,0:19:51.53,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It was a psychological condition caused \Nby an extreme distrust of others
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.53,0:19:54.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and posed no threat to his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.20,0:19:58.21,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been caused by \Nthe betrayal of those four.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.78,0:20:02.33,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Since it hadn't happened during \Nthe past several years,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.33,0:20:04.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,he believed he had recovered \Nfrom his condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.53,0:20:07.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But one month ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.28,0:20:11.06,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto was told by his doctor that \Nhe didn't have much time left to live,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.06,0:20:14.46,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,so he left on a trip with his beloved wife
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.46,0:20:17.52,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,to make his final days the \Nhappiest they could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.52,0:20:22.34,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,However, his condition caused \Na tragedy on their journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.34,0:20:24.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,They got into an accident \Nwhile on their trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.04,0:20:27.75,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,While Komoto was attempting to call an \Nambulance for his badly injured wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.75,0:20:31.02,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,he lost consciousness due to his condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.02,0:20:33.93,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and his wife passed away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.58,0:20:42.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He was still suffering the effects \Nof their betrayal ten years later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.98,0:20:46.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,And if that took the life \Nof his beloved wife,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.74,0:20:50.47,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why he sought revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.90,0:20:51.80,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.24,0:20:55.23,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,He blamed us for the death of his wife, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.76,0:20:56.85,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Save me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.09,0:20:57.92,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.49,Incoming Call,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\frz4.742\pos(309,82)}Incoming Call
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.49,sign_30246_309_Incoming_Call_Fr,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx117\fscy101\pos(342,169)\3c&H7D5F4C&}Incoming Call From\N Number-Withheld \N\NPublic Telephone
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.48,0:21:03.49,Incoming Call,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs18\frz4.735\pos(334,290)}Number-Withheld Call Settings
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.66,0:21:06.88,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.40,0:21:08.66,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It's Komoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.16,0:21:10.74,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,K-Komoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.74,0:21:15.75,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the last one left, Fuyuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.03,0:21:19.52,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,You'll pay for deceiving me ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.99,0:21:22.11,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me, Komoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.11,0:21:24.69,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I was wrong. I'll return your money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.69,0:21:27.46,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return ten times what we took, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.46,0:21:29.36,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Money, money, money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.76,0:21:31.82,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,You think you can erase your sins with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.42,0:21:35.90,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder you think you can buy \Nyour own life with money, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.36,0:21:38.92,DCItalic,KOMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the same scumbag you ever were.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.18,0:21:41.80,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,K-Komoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.26,0:21:44.43,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Komoto, hello? Komoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.43,0:21:46.49,DCMain,FUYUKI,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me, Komoto!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.82,0:21:48.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.11,0:21:50.49,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Do whatever it takes to find Komoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.79,0:21:51.49,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.09,0:21:56.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So his revenge wasn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.14,0:22:02.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but why did he bother \Nto call him this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.14,0:22:06.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's the one he hated the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.18,0:22:11.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He's the one who suggested they swindle him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.96,0:22:14.34,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's true, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.59,0:22:17.31,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Something's not right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:24:09.05,DCEpPreview,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&HE9EFF0&}Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.36,0:23:48.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one conceivable explanation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.20,0:23:52.03,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,He's got something wrapped \Naround his stomach.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.78,0:23:54.28,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,That's Mr. X?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.72,0:23:56.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,He wouldn't bother retrieving a dead body
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.81,0:24:01.33,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,or burying one in the mountains \Nunless he was really determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.69,0:24:03.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Retrieve a dead body?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.72,0:24:04.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.65,0:24:06.84,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What if he had still been alive then?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.34,0:24:08.55,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:15.05,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Out For Revenge \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.48,0:24:13.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"Out For Revenge, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Car
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.47,0:24:33.41,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint! Go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.41,0:24:34.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A car!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.56,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}I'm gonna win at the race \Ntrack and buy a new car!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.56,0:24:37.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.38,0:24:38.37,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh, my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.37,0:24:39.55,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Sounds like you lost.
